The geolocation script at the end has a bug. If the script doesn't get the right precision argument (or has other errors) it defaults to nearest thing it can figure out – in this case the country it's in. So it puts the lat/long in the middle of the USA as a default. So that's why it points to Kansas. There's lots of stories about the unfortunate people who happened to live on the farm at that default being accused of all kinds of crimes because stupid investigators thought they knew how to geolocate an IP address.
